name: BALI SWING
address: Sidan, Gianyar, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80515, Indonesia
review 1: I was initially skeptical about going to this place owing to the low number of reviews while the others had thousands of reviews. Oh boy, was I in for a pleasant surprise. The set up was magical. Overlooking a valley of rice fields and palm trees, the set up was a picture perfect Bali swing experience. The staff is extremely cooperative and put up with all the requests presented by my wife. They were patient and calm and ensured we had a great experience. Overall, it is exactly what we had envisioned and we left with our hearts full of great memories. Also, we had lunch at the restaurant overlooking the valley and the food was amazing. The host was kind enough to guide us wherever we wanted any information. Will definitely recommend everyone to give this place a try!
review 2: This place is really breath taking, I'm so amazed with the panoramic rice field view they have, so green, so natural, they have the most beautiful dress in Bali, also the staff are super kind, friendly and they take good pictures! review 4: Amazing place! Difficult to find such natural place in Bali. Tourist Destination surrounded by real nature always is touching my feelings. I would love to recommend this place to everybody who likes the food for eyes and soul altogether üíö

name: KISSIDAN ECO HILL RETREAT & RESTO
address: Jl. Raya Sidan, Sidan, Kec. Gianyar, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80515, Indonesia
review 1:
The view is spectacular. You'll get a picturesque sunset with coconut trees and rice terraces. Kissidan Eco Hill is one of a kind. It offers everything from a place to relax and quiet your mind, a place to hang out with nice drinks and picturesque view also a place for work while having traditional Indonesian food ready to be ordered. Food is delicious and served relatively quick and fresh.
You'll also get photo spots and nice surroundings...fully recommended üòäüëç
review 2:
The place is nice with lovely view of lush greeneries, flowers and rice fields.

Food options are a bit limited but the ones we ordered were quite tasty.

Staff are friendly and attentive.

Atmosphere was quiet, a distance away from the main road.

Plenty of parking.
review 3: Easy access,  nice view, healthy environment. Worth to visit ...
